article.headline: Georgia St 89, Lipscomb 81
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Playing without three starters, Georgia State rode a 26-point performance by Reo Logan to an 89-81 Atlantic Sun Conference victory over Lipscomb on Saturday. The Panthers were without all-conference forward Nate Williams (suspension), leading rebounder Trello Galloway (family funeral) and guard Lamont McIntosh (both ankles sprained). Logan, who had 10 of 15 shots, also had 8 rebounds for the Panthers (3-2, 1-1 A-Sun). Kevin Thomas and D;Andre McGrew eached added 16 points and Herman Favors 13. James Poindexter led Lipscomb (1-4) with 18 points, while Chad Hartman and Matt Jarboe each had 14 and Russell Hankins 11. GSU built an 18-point lead twice in the second half, the last at 67-49 with seven minutes remaining before the Bisons began chipping away. State sealed the victory by hitting 14 of 20 free throws in the final two minutes.
